SUMMARY *
Performs highly advanced (senior-level) human resources management tasks. Work involves directing, administering, monitoring, and evaluating the operation of a human resources department; ensuring compliance with local, state and federal laws and regulations pertaining to human resources, payroll and employment and benefits administration; management of payroll processing, employee benefits, and related training; development and maintenance of a personnel policy manual; and providing guidance and support regarding personnel management issues. Requires the ability to establish criteria, formulate projects, assess program effectiveness, and investigate and analyze a variety of extraordinary conditions, problems, and questions. Requires the ability to direct and supervise the work of others.
DISTINGUISHING CHARACTERISTICS: *
SUPERVISION RECEIVED: *
• Direct report to the Commissioners’ Court.
SUPERVISION EXERCISED: *
• Direct Reports – Human Resource employees.
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES *
Duties may include but not limited to the following:

• Directs and oversees the *operations of the Human Resources Department*; performs supervisory functions including scheduling and assignment of duties; monitors staff performance; provides guidance, support, and training to staff members; performs annual staff evaluations and takes disciplinary action as needed; monitors and manages departmental budget; prepares annual departmental budget request;

• Organizes and manages the *payroll* processing function (including interaction with vendors regarding benefits deductions), through training and oversight of HR staff, payroll systems and other resources, ensuring that employees are paid in an accurate and timely manner;

• Administers the County *Employee Benefits Package*, including annual review and renewal processes; investigates alternative resources and methodologies pertaining to employee benefits in order to help keep the County in a competitive position, while maintaining a cost-effective

HR Director Continued benefits package;
• Develops and maintains County *personnel policies*, makes recommendations for modifications, and communicates changes to employees;
• Provides accurate *information, reports* (including financial and operations reports), *and* *assistance* as required to Elected Official, Department Heads, employees, and the public regarding payroll, benefits, policies, and other HR inquiries;

• Oversees Washington County *recruiting and staffing* processes;
• Identifies *staff development* needs and resources; identifies and coordinates training resources in response to management requests; provides opportunities for professional development to all
County employees to the extent allowed by budget; ensures that HR staff members are kept up- to-date on payroll/personnel regulations and processes related to their individual job duties;

• Assist elected officials and appointed officials with interviewing, selecting, evaluating and terminating county employees, as needed and requested.

• Acts as liaison for all Washington County employees, department heads and elected officials in the resolution of employee *conflicts and grievances*;

• Researches and responds to inquiries about *employment, payroll, and personnel matters, including Unemployment and EEOC claims*;

• Ensures compliance with all Federal, State and local *employment laws* as they pertain to County operations; maintains up-to-date knowledge of changes to laws pertinent to the HR function;

• Acts as liaison with Texas County and District Retirement System and provides accurate advice and information on *county retirement programs* to employees and Commissioners Court;

• Oversees and maintains all necessary records and documentation related to HR functions in accordance with existing *records retention laws*;

• Develops and implements *special projects* to meet the needs of Washington County operations;
• Works as *part of a team* and maintains a cooperative, helpful attitude towards fellow workers, the

Commissioners’ Court, Elected Officials, Appointed Department Heads, employees and the general public;

• Maintains *confidentiality and security* of all human resources information and systems;
• Performs other duties as assigned by the Court.
PERIPHERAL DUTIES *
• Other related duties as assigned or required.
